YostaÂ express is one of the best juice outlets near Gachibowli. Quality of the juice is really good. I liked their butter scotch ice cream shake and sapota yogurt shake.
My favourite thick shake brand in Hyderabad. Dry fruit thick shake is my first choice here also Kitkat milk shake. Must try place for thickshake lovers.

Good number of options in Juices and Milkshakes. Anything served is too fresh and tastes good.
Prices could be a bit lower.
* Outdoor Seating

#FoodShaukeen #YostaExpress
Located 2 stores before rolldarbar , this is a hidden gem. We ordered kitkat ice cream shake and choco banana milk shake. Kit Kat shake was amazing and thickness was just about right. Loved it! Banana milk shake though it was good, wasn't able to enjoy it as much as the former. Kit Kat shake price 140/- and milkshake 90/-.
This is a food outlet and hardly 3 to 4 people can sit outside.
Good juice.. Fresh ones.. Love their yogurt shakes the most.. Specially the anjir and fig yogurt shake.. Recommend it to everyone. Less sugar for the health conscious guys

I was looking for some healthy and yummy banana shake because I was having a heartburn, and a craving; this place was my saviour. The thick milkshake was cold enough to relieve the burn, and yummy enough to satisfy my craving.

Seen this place while taking ORR at gachibowli and ordered a dry fruit milkshake. There was only one person in the stall. He asked me to wait and he took his time and patiently made it. After around 5 mins he delivered the milkshake. It's the best milkshake I had till date, oh boy it's so delicious I have enjoyed every sip of it. This place is a must try. This review is only based on the dry fruit milkshake. Will try other drinks on my next visit

4.5 just for three awesome yummy healthy shakes
1. Dry fruit milkshake
2. Musk melon milkshake
3. Fig milkshake
Half marks deducted for strawberry shake, though awesome, had too much ice....Â 
Late night joint, slightly heavy on pocket but its yummylicious

A small place with many list of options. Been there to taste cream shakes. butterscotch cream shake is good, Oreo is also a must try.they do have many shakes, but the Oreo will be no.1. Coming to the price it is expensive.
Don't go by the size of the shop. It serves really awesome juices. Yogurt shakes are the best. A perfect place to maintain ur health as well as satisfy ur taste buds.
Really..Yummiest Shakes..Had..Chocolate ,ButterScotch and Plum Milkshakes.Sandwiches are OK OK...PlumshakeÂ is my favourite..................................:)will order again

Yosta Xpress, the food is all about health. They serve complete hygienic and healthy food. Had plum shake and it was one of the best I had till date.
Variety of sandwiches is not much but good and healthy. 
I would suggest to try shakes for sure.

Tiny shop on a busy street with some mind blowing smoothies and shakes. Do try the seasonal fruit shakes (mango smoothie was one of the best). Really thick, well made with icecream and fruit and the couple minutes are worth the wait. Kiwi, butterscotch and KitKat were some of the good ones too.

Yosta Xpress Â is a tiny shack serving some amazing beverages and snacks in Gachibowli area. Though have seen the shop once, I didn't order anything that time. After having this really bad craving for a good milkshake today I finally decided to order something online from Yosta Xpress.
I ordered an Oreo Vanilla Milkshake whose price did at first shocked me a little as it appeared to be a little costly for a glass of milkshake. However as my order arrived and I finally got to taste the shake, the charges were quite justified. The quality and quantity of the milkshake were incredible having a thick and creamy consistency. I could taste the Vanilla ice cream with the Oreos and the combination was truly heavenly. It was indeed one of the best milkshakes I had in Hyderabad.Â 
I ordered through Zomato Online which again was like every other time delivered before their scheduled delivery time.
Best Oreo Milkshake i ever had. Visited over 100 times easily(I bet). Took almost all of my friends there. Decent sandwiches and other shakes are also good but oreo milk shake is out of the world :D

This is a pretty good place if you're looking for milkshakes.
Chocolate milkshake 4/5
Strawberry milkshake 4.5/5
Vanilla ice cream shake 3.5/5
Grape juice 2/5, I really had high hopes for this one after trying out their milkshakes but it was such a let down, the flavour of the fruit was missing.
All in all, enough to satisfy your milkshake cravings on an average budget with good quantity.

This place serve the most refreshing juices ! They keep the fruits refrigerated which makes the juice very cold ! The fruits are fresh ..a bit expensive but its soo refreshing that you will feel totally worth it !

Yosta is a good place to have thick juices/ shakes. I have personally been there many times and I feel that it is among the best juice shop in Gachibowli area. 
The juice is thick, the smoothies are creamy, the quantity is good, what else do we want.. itâ€™s just so perfectâ€¦.
Coming to ambience itâ€™s a small shop so you canâ€™t expect much from it, but the staff is courteous and friendly.
The cost is little high, when compared to other shops in the vicinity. But the quality is good so I don't care much about the cost.

Had been wanting to try this place since had heard great reviews. Tried their strawberry milkshake and it was delicious. A meal in itself. They did not have yogurt milkshakes which is what I really wanted to try so will visit again. Would love if they come up with few containing veges like cucumber/spinach etc

THIS IS THE PLACE TO BE. 
Perfect milkshakes, fast service and very reasonable, Yosta is a place for all milkshake lovers. 
Ps- Oreo Vanilla is a must try!

At first I was skeptical about visiting this place as it seemed too small and I couldn't dream of having my juices there and said myself I would probably get a tropicana juice but was I wrong,this place makes great juices ! After thoroughly reading reviews, I had a banana Milkshake which was awesome ! Looking forward to visiting again. Do pay them a visit if you're in the area, you'll not regret !hydlovesfood.blogspot.com

I ordered special of the day "strawberry banana milk shake" and it was real pleasure as I had it. The milkshake is thick and it was very soothing given the fact that I had spicy Â biryani just before that

This place was a only savior for my afternoon hunger during a Diwali holiday. I planned to visit Golconda fort and decided to grab a lunch at gachibowli. Â There were no restaurant offering service on the day of Diwali. Luckily Yosta saved me. Ordered Fig Milkshake. It was good thick milkshake ( It reminded me strawberry milkshake from McDonald). Offered in a nice cup and Â tasting good. Had good time at Golconda fort tasting this milk shake :).

Great place. I'm a regular (have some juice or shake almost everyday).
Highly recommend the kiwi juice, avocado shake and pomegranate shake. The chocolate shake is good, as well. Keep away from the watermelon juice, though, it has tasted off fairly often.

We always visit this place....banana milk shake is the best sold item here...they have fruits frozen in their refrigerator.. Milkshakes and juices are soo good here..they are thick ..and sandwiches are not that great

The best place for fresh fruit juice's..... Seethapal n mixed fruit juices are a must try..
The sandwiches are also too good...chocolate sandwich is a best to have.
Use to check in atlest 3-4 days a week....
The best juice shop in Gachibowli.Serves fresh juices,Milkshakes and yogurt shakes as well.The Oreo vanilla milkshake is the highlight for chocolate lovers.

Yosta express does give the real fruit experience. A small kiosk located along with the other food joints in front of More super market, Gachibowli. The place serves milk shakes, yogurt shakes and health boosters. 
My experiences so far have been only on the milk shakes, mainly the Sapota and Avacado (not available all the time). The shakes are quite thick but again not over done. The most fascinating aspect is no ice is added and because the fruits are stored in the freezer you get the cold nature. They do add ice cream in most of the shakes apart from sugar. 
Hygienic and well maintained place considering how small space Yosta is running in. No seating space as such so preferably orders should be take away. Pricing is very affordable a juice would not cost more than 80 rupees. 
Need to try out the other shakes especially the Custard apple and the health boosters.

To quench the thirst and to maintain the gluco level Juice is one of best solution recommended.
So if you are near by Gachibowli flyover and your gluco meter is down you can have a quick break at yosta to bring back the level.
It's a small counter serving varieties of juices and shakes.
I love there banner pasted inside the counter which explain the  benefits of different fruits.
Me n my colleague ordered Black grapes juice which was very tasty and have very good health benefits, which act as antioxidant.
Setvice is good and prompt Must visit place.
Overall good experience.
Cheers!!!
Amir
Very good juices and milkshakes it's next to Rice Bowl near Gachibowli it's a quick stop after having rice bowl for delicious milkshakes.........
A small outlet in front of more super market . they make tasty milk shakes .sitaphal milk shake is their speciality .  will give 4/5 for their quality and taste.

Yosta was my saviour for the daily dose of fresh juices and shakes when I relocated from Mumbai to Hyderabad and I have been a regular since then. The team, the owner brothers, and Bitto and Raju have been meticulous in serving me, even remembering my choice of sugarless juices. Not only me, but also my wife, who is very picky about the service, can't stop raving about Yosta.
Yosta's juices and shakes contain real fresh fruits, no added flavours. And mind it, these are very much unlike the runny, watery juices that you usually get. 
Apart from drinks, they serve sandwiches too.
My take, if you are hungry and happen to be in Gachibowli, and want to eat without hurting your tummy as well as the wallet, Yosta would be the best bet. One sandwich and a shake, and you will be more than full.
Cheers and best wishes to the team!
P.S. Yosta is accessible via FoodPanda too. So, you need not necessarily be in the vicinity you see.ðŸ˜Š

What could be a better way to quench your summer thirst than having chilled fruit juices. This small outlet sits in the blazing sun and churns out chilled fruit juice blended right in front of your eyes. No adulteration is their plus point, you can ask them to not add sugar and you get a glassfull of nice summer cooler.
The quantity is nice which makes it good VFM and the availability is rarely an issue here. I've tried a couple of yogurt shakes as well and they were good too.
They have standardized measured proportions so consistency is also not an issue here the only variations you might get is due to the fruit itself (though most of the times I found the fruits fresh and tasty)
I would definitely recommend this as a great hangout spot for the summers!

Situated next to Rice Bowl, this place serves Juices, Milk Shakes, Yogurt Shakes and Healthy Boosters. Ordered for Chikoo Yoghurt Shake and Musk Melon Milk Shake. Was a bit disappointed with Musk Melon but Chikoo was good. Not everyone can njoy the taste of Yoghurt based Shakes. This one is quite good.
Ambience: N/A
Service: 3.5/5
Food: 3/5
Great place for milk shakes around 60 to 80 rupees,  reasonable pricing best in terms of taste... What i really liked here is they don't use ice.. try out when you carve for juices  ðŸ˜‹

A perfect place for fresh juices n milk shakes ,this place is beside rice bowl in a small kiosk in front of more super market.
They hav a big menu but half of them Wil be available.but whatever they serve r fresh fruit juices n thick milk shakes.
Pricing on avg is about 60-80 for milk shakes n 30-40 for juices.quantity is good but the service is little slow .

This is one my favourite place at Gachibowli     ,I regularly have their milkshakes they doesn't add any water or flavours in it .Great about this place is that they still maintaining the same quality keep it up guyz.

Going by the looks, this place can be passed off as any another juice center. But, the juices and shakes available in store can surprise you literally.
Located in front of More super market, right after Police commissioner office in Gachibowli. If it helps, this place is just beside the Rice Bowl.
This place actually serves some seriously thick shakes. The shakes are available in 2 types, yogurt based and milk based. All the shakes are not overdone to get the thickness, the fruit flavor is intact. Each gulp soothes the way in. I have tasted almost all the shakes, but favorites being Banana shake and Sapota shake.
Recently, I tasted the  Avacado shake which is also good. This is not part of their menu, available only for that day/select days.Â 
The owner of this place is very friendly person. Got to know from him, some of the fruits they use like Banana (Chakkara Keli variety) and Sapotas are imported from Guntur. All the fruits are freezed which brings in the coldness to the shake. No ice is used.
Considering the taste and quality wise, this place is total VFM. My place to go for to savor fruit shakes.
One of the best juice shops I totally rely on ... Almost everyday. They do not compromise on quality. Menu is short and sweet. With no artificial stuff and ice u can't ask more.

Just came back from this outlet at gachibowli.
Those men serving there were from my state orissa. Felt homely seeing that.
Coming to food, ordered for paneer sandwich, chicken Sandwich and pineapple juice.
Paneer and chicken Sandwich were,  the stuffing ( paneer and chicken respectively) with sliced onions and capsicum along with a mayonnaise addition. It was obviously , bit cheesy, plain though not completely and good to have. Liked it. 
Chicken in chicken Sandwich could've been a boiled for some more time to avoid the thread like texture which reduces the interest to chew and eat.
When added with tomato ketchup, plainness can be reduced and we can get ourselves a tastier sandwich :-) 
Again a common problem with sandwich is that when we take a bite , the stuffings come out from the sides, which is sometimes irritating. So, they could've given a thick sandwich so that when we hold the sides firmly the bread doesn't get torn off. Or if you have a better way to serve, a better solution, it'll be most welcomed. :-) please consider .
Next, pineapple juice- I felt it was pure and desi kind of. 
Pure because it was a bit thick and they didn't filter out the skin completely. No its not a criticism but that's the way it's served in villages, which is the mark of originality or tradition , as it was before and Ofcorse which isn't unhealthy.
In truest terms , I mean, the solid residues after crushing the pineapple in mixer, were there in my drink. But wasn't bad. I liked it. Liked the thickness, which wasn't too thick to pass through food pipe nor was it like water or having zero thickness.
For Pineapple juice- 3.5
Paneer sandwich- 3.4
Chicken Sandwich- 3.2
Overally I would give 3.3
Not to be preferred if ambience is very important as it's a small outlet with some chairs in front as the only arrangement.
one of the best place at reasonable price.. Its like you name it and you get it.. Seasonal fruit shakes are the most awaited ones.. Should try it at least once..
